# CodeRabbit Demo

This repo showcases CodeRabbit code review. PRs should touch multiple files.

## What each PR should exercise
- Security: hardcoded secrets, missing auth
- Logic bugs: off-by-one streaks, bad schedule math
- Missing error handling, N+1 queries, missing tests, migration risks

## When asked to "plant a bug"
- Make it subtle and realistic (not syntax errors)
- Touch 2+ files so review breadth is visible
- Document the expected CodeRabbit finding in the PR description (not in code comments)

## PR hygiene
- Branch per feature; run `make test` and `ruff check` before push
- Keep `.coderabbit.yaml` path instructions in sync when adding new layers
